In [3]:
#Get the time difference between purchase time and signup time
data['signup_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data.signup_time)
data['purchase_time'] = pd.to_datetime(data.purchase_time)
time_diff = data['purchase_time'] - data['signup_time']
time_diff = time_diff.apply(lambda x: x.seconds)
data['time_diff'] = time_diff
data= pd.get_dummies(data,columns=['source','browser','sex'])
data.head()

In [11]:
import sklearn.model_selection
seed = 999
x= data_model.loc[:,data_model.columns != 'class']
y = data_model['class']

# split into training dataset and test dataset
xtrain,xtest,ytrain,ytest = sklearn.model_selection.train_test_split(x,y,test_size=0.3,random_state=seed)
#trai
In [14]:
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier,export_graphviz

dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3,min_samples_leaf=20,min_samples_split=20)
dt.fit(xtrain,ytrain)
export_graphviz(dt,
                     out_file='tree.dot',

                     feature_names=x.columns,class_names=['NotFraud','Fraud'],
                proportion=True,leaves_parallel=True,filled=True)

from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, roc_curve, auc,confusion_matrix
print('------classification_report------')
print(classification_report(ytrain, dt.predict(xtrain)))
print('------confusion matrix------')
print(confusion_matrix(ytrain ,dt.predict(xtrain)))

  1. geting more features

Forecast fraud loss¶

In [22]:
#forecast steps:
#1.apply model to existing data
#2.loss=Probablity of fraud* transaction_amt

y_hats=dt.predict(x)
data_model['yhats']=y_hats
data_model['exp_fraud_loss']=data_model['yhats']*data_model['purchase_value']
print('expected loss :' , data_model['exp_fraud_loss'].sum(),'total transaction amount :', data_model['purchase_value'].sum())

expected loss : 280911 total transaction amount : 5581378
